---
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro'

const bookingHref = 'https://cal.com/builtbywin/20-min-ai-sprint-fit-call'
---

<BlogLayout
  title="work with me"
  description="A four-week AI app sprint for business owners who want to build and ship with AI coding tools"
  pathSegments={[{ name: 'work-with-me', href: null }]}
  backHref="/ston"
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>work-with-me/</h1>
    <p class="page-description">1:1 ai coding coaching for business owners</p>
  </header>

  <section class="hero">
    <h2>build your app and learn how to keep shipping it</h2>
    <p>
      i work 1:1 with business owners on their real app, internal tool, or product idea. over four
      weeks, we set up the right ai coding workflow and ship one useful feature together.
    </p>
    <a class="primary-cta" href={bookingHref} data-work-with-me-cta="hero">
      book a free 20-minute call →
    </a>
    <p class="availability">4 weeks · $1,500 · three founding-client spots</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>the 4-week ai app sprint</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>four weekly 1:1 working sessions on your project</li>
      <li>setup for claude code, codex, your repository, and the tools around them</li>
      <li>a practical workflow for planning, prompting, reviewing, debugging, and deploying</li>
      <li>one real feature planned, built, reviewed, and shipped together</li>
      <li>async help between sessions when you get stuck</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>what you leave with</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>a working ai coding environment set up around your app</li>
      <li>a shipped feature—not another tutorial project</li>
      <li>a repeatable way to make changes without guessing</li>
      <li>the ability to keep building without waiting on me for every update</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>this is for you if</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>you run a business and have an app idea, an existing app, or an internal tool to build</li>
      <li>you want to make changes yourself instead of waiting on a developer for every update</li>
      <li>you have tried ai coding tools but keep getting stuck, breaking things, or losing track of the work</li>
      <li>you learn best by working on your own project with someone beside you</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted">
      this is hands-on coaching, not a passive course or a full-service development agency.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>why me</h2>
    <p>
      i build apps with coding agents every day. i made
      <a href="https://back2vibing.builtby.win/">back2vibing</a> to manage several agent sessions
      at once, and i write openly about
      <a href="/ston/blog/2026-07-14/parallel-agents-worktrees-tmux">the workflow and where it still breaks</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      before building my own products, i led full-stack and cross-functional projects at doordash,
      including a 15-person engineering and legal effort for the germany launch. i can help with
      both sides: setting up the tools and making sure the work actually ships.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>what happens next</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>book a call and tell me what you are building, what you have tried, and where you are stuck</li>
      <li>we spend 20 minutes deciding whether the sprint fits</li>
      <li>if it does, i send the scope, start date, and payment link</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="final-cta">
    <h2>want to ship something real in the next four weeks?</h2>
    <p>bring your app, your idea, or the broken workflow. we will work on the real thing.</p>
    <a class="primary-cta" href={bookingHref} data-work-with-me-cta="footer">
      book a free 20-minute call →
    </a>
  </section>
</BlogLayout>

<script is:inline>
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-work-with-me-cta]').forEach((link) => {
    link.addEventListener('click', () => {
      window.posthog?.capture('work_with_me_cta_clicked', {
        cta_location: link.getAttribute('data-work-with-me-cta'),
        offer: 'ai_app_sprint',
        price_usd: 1500,
      })
    })
  })
</script>

<style>
  .page-header,
  .hero,
  section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .page-header h1,
  h2 {
    color: var(--color-term-dir);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .page-description,
  .availability,
  .muted {
    color: var(--color-term-fg-muted);
  }

  .page-description,
  .availability {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hero {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-term-dir);
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  p,
  li {
    font-size: 0.925rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  ul,
  ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  ul {
    list-style: disc;
  }

  ol {
    list-style: decimal;
  }

  li + li {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--color-term-link);
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .primary-cta {
    display: inline-block;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.7rem 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-term-bg);
    background: var(--color-term-dir);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-term-dir);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .primary-cta:hover,
  .primary-cta:focus-visible {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--color-term-dir);
  }

  .muted {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .final-cta {
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-term-bg-lighter);
  }

  @media (max-width: 40rem) {
    .primary-cta {
      display: block;
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
</style>
